Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content:
@webworker01, have you considered linking people to ZecProxy and giving instructions on how to use it?

It is a great way for people to boost their mining speed and it can only help the pool overall if people know how to use it.

Also, may want to consider native zstratum addresses for the pool.

Anyway, here is a link to the GitHub repo:

https://github.com/BScrk/zecproxy

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: never seen that, looks pretty interesting

Author: Alright#0419
Content: don't understand how a proxy will increase shares

Author: Alright#0419
Content: I used a different proxy for a while and didn't notice a difference

Author: Alright#0419
Content: only with like 1.5ksol though

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: It is a local host proxy so not a real proxy. However, it also uses zstratum (which is optimized for equihash) rather than the standard stratum protocol.

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it probably prevents stale shares by having one persistent connection that instantly syncs with peers on a local network, would be my guess

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: I suppose it is more about latency. It reduces the connections and feeds your mining software packets optimized for equihash rather than a standard hashing algo.

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: The proxy or the protocol?

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content:
I am already using the proxy successfully but it may be cross compatible with standard stratum. Either way, here is the zstratum changes:

https://github.com/slushpool/poclbm-zcash/wiki/Stratum-protocol-changes-for-ZCash

As you can see, slushpool implements it.

I believe optiminer has native support for zstratum and zstratum over TLS.

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: I believe the proxy converts a standard stratum pool to zstratum.

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: Which is why I can use it.

Author: CryptoFoxGaming#5228
Content: The proxy supports TLS in the options.
